description: A gem-bearer is being held in a secret lab, and it's up to THE 99 to rescue him! But can THE 99 really "fight for peace" or is Dr. Ramzi due for a lesson in humility as he readies a strike force against the best advice of his team. And it's THE 99 who will pay the price for his arrogance...

It's all-out action as Raqib the Watcher's new 99 team launches a rescue mission to save Jabbar, Noora, Darr and Mumita from the clutches of the Pathologist! But when old-meets-new to strike back, are the heroes playing into Rughal's nefarious scheme to bait THE 99 into temptation-- using their own powers?

Dr. Ramzi wants the world to know about the fantastic new super heroes called The 99, however, their parents don't. Caught between their well intentioned parents and the desire to put their newly acquired powers to use the teens think they have a solution that will protect their families and their identities but will their plan of HIDING IN PLAIN SIGHT work?

The 99 face their deadliest challenge yet in the darkness of the Philippine jungles. Sent to rescue kidnapped aid workers, members of The 99 come face to face with the Death Merchant. Can Jabbar's super-strength overcome this evil or is there some other power at work here? Introducing the newest gem-bearer, Widad.

Locked in a deadly standoff the police and The 99 face down a savage smuggler known as the Death Merchant. In the blink of an eye he takes a hostage and escapes further into the jungle. Hadya's tracking abilities can find him, Fattah can transport them there in an instant and Jabbar can provide the muscle but this triad isn't quite right for overcoming the Death Merchant's particular brand of evil.

Stalked and hunted by an unknown enemy, Raqib the Watcher warns Ramzi and The 99 about the mysterious figure know as Rughal. The 99 choose not hide within the safety of their headquarters but instead go to the aid of elephants being illegally hunted in Zimbabwe. While stalking poachers in the bush an unseen weapon attacks Jabbar, is this the work of Rughal?

In a surprise move a gem-bearer relinquishes their Noor Stone and the powers that go with it. Rughal's mystery weapon attempts to attack Dr. Ramzi, but finds easier prey, it's not only someone the members of The 99 trust, but, someone no longer protected by the power of a Noor Stone.

Possessed by Rughal's fiendish weapon Blair Davis makes off with the Noor Stones belonging to members of The 99. Suddenly, the 99 Steps Foundation is under attack, Hammerfist, The Savage, The Sphinx, The Pathologist and Dr. Nanno are under Rughal's orders to capture the Noor Stones. Without their gems can the members of The 99 repel the attack or are they POWERLESS?

The power of the Noor Stones, Rughal wants it but even he can't define it or truly understand how they work. And, despite the efforts of Dr Nanno and The Pathologist to harness Noor Stone energy, they remain empty-handed. That's when they call in the world's leading scientific expert of Noor Stone analysis Jami the Assembler, kidnapped from the 99 Steps Foundation and put to work for Rughal.

Dr. Ramzi wants the world to know about the fantastic new super heroes called The 99, however, their parents don't. Caught between their well intentioned parents and the desire to put their newly acquired powers to use the teens think they have a solution that will protect their families and their identities but will their plan of HIDING IN PLAIN SIGHT work?
The 99 take the fight to Rughal within his Hong Kong fortress. Untested in battle and outnumbered by his Drone Warriors, can the power of the 99's triads defeat Rughal's forces?

Jabbar the Powerful's little sister wants in on the superhero adventure and forms her own superhero team with the youngest and newest members of The 99. There's a gem-bearer in trouble beneath the streets of Paris - but what can a couple of kids do? Find out as we introduce, the Junior 99!

A team of 99 members is off to Cambodia to assist in a village's de-mining operation. On their mission they find that while their masks protect their identities, the masks place a barrier between them and the people they are trying to protect.
Chaos and confusion reign at the 99 Steps Foundation as the media breaks the news of The 99 member's true identities. Meanwhile, new gem-bearers are almost literally popping out of the woodwork.
Noora the Light's father has been kidnapped and is being held for ransom, but it's not money the kidnapper wants, it's Noora and the power of her Noor Stone. Special: Manga back-up feature.

Giant Robot wreaking havoc on the streets of Paris, whom do you call? The 99. But what do you do if Jami the Assembler created the robot? When Jami creates F.R.A.N.K.I.E. to protect the 99 Steps Foundation the robot's logic board acts a little too logically sending it on a misguided mission to render inactive all the gem-bearers in proximity.

The ancient city of Bam is burning and Buran's nephew is missing. Meanwhile in Paris, The 99's newest member Sami the Listener is also missing. Dr. Ramzi sends out two teams to locate the missing teens. The team that is sent to Bam discovers a new gem-bearer with a fiery ability, the other team discovers...
Sent searching for Sami-- Hadya, Noora and Fattah find him at a retreat hidden high in the Himalayas, but he's not the only gem-bearer they find there.

Guided to the retreat by his students, Dr. Ramzi meets his counterpart in Madame Deneuve, a former gem-bearer who has developed the retreat as a haven for gem-bearers and others with special abilities. Here, like Ramzi's foundation the gem-bearers are encouraged to develop their gifts in peaceful surroundings. But something sinister is lurking and evil is revealed as Blackwolf and the Sphinx rear their ugly heads.
The 99 issue #24!

Deep beneath the Artic Circle a researcher is trapped in a small submarine and running out of air. It's cold, dark and extremely dangerous with an underwater volcano that is about to blow as Dr. Ramzi sends two triad teams beneath the surface. Introducing the newest member of The 99, Mukit the Nourisher.

Things are really rockin' in Seville, where the 99 Steps Foundation is throwing a party to get to know their new neighbors. The problem is, it isn't just the band that's doing the rockin' but Tremor, a villain with some earth shaking abilities. Oh, and there's an 800 pound gorilla in the room too.

First Rughal, then Blackwolf show up at the 99 Steps Foundation, they come not bearing arms but rather, seeking assistance. Rughal seeks approval, claiming he's reformed his evil ways and is starting his own team of gem-bearers. Blackwolf brings his son whom he believes is a gem-bearer in need of assistance. Mystery and confusion rule the night amid rumors of a traitor among The 99.

Is there a traitor in THE 99's headquarters? Dr. Ramzi is tricked into dispersing THE 99 into small teams around the world, leaving headquarters unprotected and open to attack by the nefarious Blackwolf and the Sphinx! Plus, the identity of the mysterious Sphinx is revealed!

Blackwolf and the Sphinx have trapped Dr. Ramzi in THE 99's headquarters in Seville! THE 99 teams up with their old enemy, Rughal, to rescue him and reclaim their home. While Rughal faces off with his former protégé, the team learns that Blackwolf's adopted son is dying-and only Rughal holds the key to saving his life!

Could one of THE 99's own be...a criminal? A secret from Mumita's past catches up with her in Venice. How can THE 99 help one of its own if she's actually guilty? Justice must be done as THE 99 race against time to save the floating city from a flood, while Mumita faces the authorities alone.

Meet Baseer the All-Seeing, German boy detective, as he joins THE 99 to search for a lost rocket, which mysteriously disappeared from radar moments after a successful launch. But can THE 99 trust someone they just met? Is Baseer all that he seems? And can the lost rocket be found, or will the whole project come crashing down?

Time for a celebration as THE 99 welcomes three new members to the team! But then things start to go wrong. How can THE 99 headquarters be attacking each hero separately with a trap built to neutralize each gem-bearer? Can the heroes fight alone...against their own house? Could an old enemy be behind this specialized attack?

Jami the Assembler's own security protocols have trapped THE 99 members inside their own headquarters! As they struggle to defeat Jami's clever devices, Noora works to get past a murky barrier of another kind--does it hold the clue to who is behind this assault on THE 99? Find out as this house party winds down!

EVE OF DESTRUCTION

Traffic lights stop working, machines are broken--networked devices all over Europe are compromised, just like the network in THE 99's own headquarters last issue! Whatever was in THE 99's system has found its way into the wider world. Meanwhile, Aleem has a vision--THE 99, all lying as if dead inside their own training bunker! THE JUNIOR 99 act, in secret, to investigate. But when newcomer Raheema the Merciful takes over the team from Jabbar's sister Noaf, will her mistake spell doom for the team, including Dr. Ramzi? Also, in back-up story FIRST CONTACT, Jami, Mumita, and Hafiz try to stop farm machinery running amok--and finally, Jami ties in the energy signature to one they're seen before--when they were searching for a rocket in outer space!

Take a trip back in time to Riverdale Middle School with The New Archies! Archie, Betty, Veronica and the whole gang were just as goofy then as they are now as high school students! Follow their wacky adventures in this 100-page Digital Exclusive collection. Can Ms. Grundy keep her class under control?

Before Venom, before Carnage...there was Dr. Octopus. One of Spiderman's most dangerous and interesting villains. This book is from the "Marvel House of Ideas" series which reprints the Spiderman's first clash with the good doctor as well as many other battles including Spiderman's first contact with the PUNISHER. A must for all Spiderman fans. For those seeking the new, computer generated artwork which is making Marvel famous in the 90's and beyond, this book may disappoint them. But fear not, these classic stories are the real reason why you should have this book.
